        '**Pre-shoot planning call** + on-site scout (Tarragona area) to identify the best hiding spots and light direction.',
        '**2-2.5 hours of coverage on the day**: discreet photography of the moment + an extra 45-60 minutes of **full couple session** after the "yes" (walk, hugs, looks, ring close-ups, environmental portraits).',
        '**Optional video of the moment** (second crew member) — a second camera with directional audio to capture the "yes".',
        '**Fast WhatsApp selection** in under 2 hours. 5-10 photos so you can share that same night.',
        '**Full online gallery** in 7 days with **30-50 edited photos** in high resolution — the moment, the reaction, and the couple session. No watermark, free download.',
      ],
    },
    locations: {
      title: 'Location ideas around Tarragona',
      intro:
        'Tarragona has settings that almost feel designed for a proposal. A few of our favourite spots:',
      bullets: [
        '**Tamarit beach and castle** — sunset at the castle with the Mediterranean behind. One of the most requested for its raw photogenic quality.',
        '**Balcó del Mediterrani and the Roman amphitheatre** — central Tarragona carries 2,000 years of history. Works particularly well for travellers who want an iconic-recognisable Tarragona shot.',
        '**Cala Romana / Cala Fonda** — quieter, less crowded. Great for private proposals in the morning or early afternoon.',
        '**Priorat or Costers del Segre vineyards** — if your partner loves wine or nature, walking through vines in low golden light is hard to beat.',
        '**Siurana or Prades** — for film-set drama with cliffs and a medieval village. Car needed and a short walk.',
      ],
      footnote:
        "And if you have a place that means something personal to the two of you (the café where you met, the beach of your first kiss) — even better. The story beats the postcard.",
    },
    midCta: {
      copy: "If you've got a date and a location in mind, we'll confirm availability over WhatsApp the same day. Still deciding? Also fine — we plan it together.",
      button: 'Message us on WhatsApp',
    },
    travelers: {
      title: 'Flying to Tarragona just for the proposal?',
      intro:
        'Roughly one in four proposals we shoot is for a couple who flies in for the moment itself. We\'ve covered couples from the UK, US, Netherlands, and Germany. Here\'s how it works for travellers:',
      bullets: [
        '**Planning call in English or Spanish** before you travel, to agree on the location, the time, and the rain plan B.',
        '**Curated location shortlist** based on what time of day you land and the aesthetic you\'re after (sea, ruins, vineyards, mountain). We send photos of each so you can pick before boarding the plane.',
        '**Optional airport pickup and walk-in** from Reus airport or central Tarragona, so you don\'t get lost before the moment.',
      ],
    },
    videos: {
      title: 'See how our proposals look',
      intro: 'Three minutes on YouTube — a couple of full proposal stories in landscape, and two vertical clips of the moment itself.',
      moreLabel: 'More videos on our channel',
      playLabel: 'Play video',
    },
    session: {
      title: "It's a full couple session, not just the moment",
      body: "Once we step out from our hiding spot, we don't shoot a quick formal portrait and leave. After the 'yes' you get **45-60 more minutes**: the first hug with the ring, the looks down at the new hand, the nervous laughter, a walk through the area, ring close-ups, environmental portraits. **You'll walk away with 30-50 photos of the day**, not 5 of the moment.",
    },
    faqTitle: 'Common questions about proposal photography',
    faqs: [
      {
        q: 'How do you hide without your partner spotting you?',
        a: "We arrive 60-90 minutes early. We post ourselves along the route you've shared, far enough away to shoot with a telephoto (200-400mm) without entering your partner's field of view. If the spot has people, we blend in like any tourist with a camera.",
      },
      {
        q: 'When should I book?',
        a: "Ideally 3-4 weeks in advance, but we've covered proposals with 5 days' notice. The more time you give us, the better we can scout the location and identify the best hiding angles.",
      },
      {
        q: 'What if it rains?',
        a: "If a plan B is viable (a covered location or under trees), we use it. If your proposal depends on a specific setting (sunset at Tamarit castle, for example), we suggest rescheduling to the next clear day — no cost if you let us know more than 24h ahead.",
      },
      {
        q: 'When do I get the photos?',
        a: "An online gallery with every edited photo within **7 days**. If you ask for a fast selection to show family that same night, we send 5-10 photos within 2 hours over WhatsApp.",
      },
      {
        q: 'What if she says no?',
        a: "It's never happened in 3 years of running this service. If it did, we'd hand over the session without invoicing — that's not a moment to charge anyone for.",
      },
      {
        q: "We're flying in — what does the planning look like for a Tarragona-only trip?",
        a: 'This is one of the reasons we offer the service. We do a short planning call in English, Spanish, or Catalan to agree on the exact location and timing. We keep a curated list of go-to spots in Tamarit, the Costa Daurada, and Roman Tarragona that work especially well for travellers.',
      },
    ],
    finalCta: {
      h2: 'Have a date in mind?',
      body: "Message us on WhatsApp and we'll confirm availability the same day. If you're still deciding the where and when, message us anyway — we plan it together.",
      primary: 'WhatsApp us',
      secondary: '1-minute quiz',
    },
    quizPath: '/en/quiz',
    whatsAppMessage:
      "Hi! I'm planning a proposal in the Tarragona area and would like to talk about availability and how the service works.",
    breadcrumbCurrent: 'Proposal photography',
  },
};

const c = COPY[lang];

const waLink = `${WHATSAPP_BASE}&text=${encodeURIComponent(c.whatsAppMessage)}`;
const canonicalUrl = `${SITE.url}${langPath}/peticion-de-mano`;

const jsonLd = [
  breadcrumbJsonLd([
    { name: t('schema.breadcrumb.home'), url: `${SITE.url}${langPath}/` },
    { name: c.breadcrumbCurrent, url: canonicalUrl },
  ]),
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'Service',
    name: c.meta.title.split(' | ')[0],
    description: c.meta.description,
    provider: { '@type': 'LocalBusiness', name: 'Lifetime Weddings', url: SITE.url },
    areaServed: { '@type': 'AdministrativeArea', name: 'Tarragona, Catalonia, Spain' },
    serviceType: 'Proposal photography',
    url: canonicalUrl,
  },
  {
    '@context': 'https://schema.org',
    '@type': 'FAQPage',
    mainEntity: c.faqs.map((f) => ({
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: f.q,
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: f.a },
    })),
  },
];

/** Render a copy snippet that may contain **bold** Markdown markers. */
function renderBold(s: string): string {
  return s.replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>');
}
---

<BaseLayout
  lang={lang}
  title={c.meta.title}
  description={c.meta.description}
  canonicalPath="/peticion-de-mano"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  ogImage={heroImg}
  ogType="article"
